Los Angeles (dpa) – US comedian and actor Kevin Hart has been hospitalized with “major back injuries” after he was involved in a car accident in California on Sunday, local media reported. California Highway Patrol told CBS Los Angeles that the accident took place after the driver of Hart’s 1970 Plymouth Barracuda lost control and the car rolled down an embankment early Sunday morning. The “Night School” star and the driver were hospitalized and were being treated for “major back injuries,” CBS said. A second passenger was reported to have sustained minor injuries. The California Highway Patrol said that the driver was not under the influence of alcohol.